headline: Clorox (NYSE:CLX) Raises Earnings Guidance Despite 1% Dip in Sales
summary: Clorox (NYSE:CLX) recently reported a robust recovery in earnings, including a third-quarter net income jump to $186 million, up from a net loss a year ago. This upbeat financial performance comes amidst the company's revised earnings guidance, reflecting optimism for organic sales growth despite headwinds from divestitures.
